parent_catalog_academic_advising_continu.text:
Meet with the department of their major prior to registration;

Become familiar and keep up with University Honors requirements. These can be found on the BHC website;

Contact an academic advisor in the Office of Honors Advising and based on the recommendation from their major department and the requirements for University Honors, an Honors Advisor can assist with Honors course selection;

Continue to register for classes online;

Check their class schedule on myUCF to ensure its accuracy; and,

Attend any mandatory BHC advising appointments.

parent_catalog_academic_advising_new_stu.text:
Receive information from their assigned CAHSA Academic Success Coach prior to orientation and meet with their assigned CAHSA Academic Success Coach in a group setting during orientation to discuss college policies and procedures;

Meet with a major advisor during orientation to discuss major requirements, plan their class schedule, and learn more about the majors offered;

Register for classes during orientation at a central location with the help of their assigned CAHSA Academic Success Coach

Check their "Fee Invoices" to ensure accuracy of their class schedule; and,

Reach out to their assigned CAHSA ASC following orientation with any additional questions or concerns.

parent_catalog_academic_advising_continu.text:
Meet with their assigned CAHSA Academic Success Coach on a regular basis. Students will receive an invitation to their UCF Email account to schedule their CAHSA Academic Success Coaching advising appointment through our online appointment scheduling system, myKnight STAR. The CAHSA Academic Success Coach will assist each student in updating their Pegasus Path plans to support progression towards four-year graduation for FTIC students and three-year graduation for transfer students;

Meet with their major advisor in their department or school, when relevant, to review their academic progress and to create a plan of study for subsequent semesters. Review this plan each term with their major advisor and prior to registration;

Review and update their Pegasus Path plan and review their myKnight degree audit at least every term and understand all degree requirements;

Regularly check and respond to emails received to their UCF Email account and respond to prompts to complete CAHSA and major advising sessions each semester.

parent_catalog_academic_advising_new_stu.text:
Be classified as a 'pre-major' until admission to the major requirements are met and a change of major request has been processed. 'Pre-major' students have enrollment access to CBA non-restricted classes and do not have enrollment access to CBA restricted classes;

Meet college Academic Success Coaches in a group setting during Orientation to discuss admission to the major requirements, college policy, procedures, expectations, and degree programs;

Review degree requirements at Orientation using the Degree Audit and CBA literature to better understand degree requirements and the various components of their Degree Audit;

Submit all requests to evaluate transfer courses for equivalency to UCF courses during their first term of enrollment at UCF. General Education coursework is evaluated for equivalency by Academic Services, while the Business Common Program Prerequisites and all business coursework is evaluated for equivalency by the College;

Meet with a Career Coach in the OPD (BA2, Room 101), to understand the career options of their major; and,

Meet with the Academic Success Coaching Team in the OPD (BA2, Room 101), to review academic progress and develop or update an academic plan..

parent_catalog_academic_advising_continu.text:
Meet with the Academic Success Coaching Team to review academic progress and develop or update an academic plan. Degree requirements and course prerequisites should be reviewed prior to registration each term;

Meet with a Career Coach as directed by activities in the college's Career Professionalism curriculum;

Register for courses in myUCF at their scheduled appointment time. All changes to the student's class schedule must be completed by the end of the add/drop/swap period;

Be classified as 'pre-major' until admission to the major requirements are met and a change of major request has been processed. 'Pre-major' students have enrollment access to CBA non-restricted classes and do not have enrollment access to CBA restricted classes;

Meet with the Academic Success Coaching Team during the term prior to their anticipated graduation term as needed; and,

File the electronic "Intent to Graduate Form" by the end of the term prior to the term in which graduation is intended.

Students placed on 'Lack of Progress' (LOP) due to Major and/or College of Business Administration GPA concerns will:

Have a "hold" placed on their subsequent registration; and,

Meet with their dedicated Academic Success Coach to review the student's academic situation and develop a plan of action; and,

Complete the CBA Academic Standing webcourse and any subsequent requirements.

